&lt;h1&gt;Respiratory Ward - Medical Division&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Senior Sister/ Senior Charge Nurse, Band 7&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to internal promotion we have an exciting opportunity for an experienced Senior Nurse who wishes to develop their management and leadership skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Respiratory is a 33 bedded ward, which includes 4 high care beds and has a friendly and highly motivated nursing team, supported by an exceptional medical team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone with energy and enthusiasm to drive forward the Bath Improvement System methodology and to engage the whole MDT in improving the quality, safety and patient experience on Respiratory Ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strong leadership and performance management is an integral aspect of this role and you will be supported by a Matron and the divisional Senior Nursing team to develop your own leadership skills and developing your future career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must have a proven track record of progressive leadership and development, both of staff and services. We are looking for an individual with at least 2 years of band 6 ward experience or a senior nurse with other relevant service improvement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Matron Melanie Evans (01225 826866) or email:melanie.evans16@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
